Body with several peudopores on various positions (
Fig. 4D
).

Tibiotarsi I, II and III with 18, 18 and 16 chaetae respectively (
Fig. 5G
). No clavate tenent hairs. Claw with a very small median tooth (
Figs 5G
; 
6E
).

Furcula fully developed, dens with 3 chaetae each, mucro large even if slightly fused with the dens (stage 1 - stage 2 according to 
Cassagnau 1958
) (
Fig. 6F
). Tenaculum present with 2+ 2 teeth.
